HEADWORD: Cabrerite
<hw>Ca*brer"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>An apple-green mineral, a hydrous arseniate of nickel, cobalt, and
magnesia; -- so named from the Sierra <etsep>Cabrera</etsep>,
Spain.</def>⟦br⟧
